Report a descriptive table

Source: R/report_table.R
report_table.Rd

Creates tables to describe different objects (see list of supported objects in report).

report_table(x, ...)

Arguments

x

The R object that you want to report (see list of of supported objects above).
...

Arguments passed to or from other methods.

Value

A data.frame.

Examples

library(report)

# Miscellaneous
r <- report_table(sessionInfo())
r

# Data
report_table(iris$Sepal.Length)

#> Mean |   SD | Median |  MAD |  Min |  Max | n_Obs | Skewness | Kurtosis | percentage_Missing
#> --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> 5.84 | 0.83 |   5.80 | 1.04 | 4.30 | 7.90 |   150 |     0.31 |    -0.55 |               0.00
report_table(as.character(round(iris$Sepal.Length, 1)))

#> n_Entries | n_Obs | n_Missing | percentage_Missing
#> --------------------------------------------------
#> 35.00     |   150 |         0 |               0.00
report_table(iris$Species)

#> Level      | n_Obs | percentage_Obs
#> -----------------------------------
#> setosa     |    50 |          33.33
#> versicolor |    50 |          33.33
#> virginica  |    50 |          33.33
report_table(iris)

# h-tests
report_table(t.test(mpg ~ am, data = mtcars))

#> Parameter | Group | Mean_Group1 | Mean_Group2 | Difference | t(18.33) |     p |              CI |                  Method |     d |           d CI
#> --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> mpg       |    am |       17.15 |       24.39 |       7.24 |    -3.77 | 0.001 | [-11.28, -3.21] | Welch Two Sample t-test | -1.76 | [-2.82, -0.67]
report_table(cor.test(iris$Sepal.Length, iris$Sepal.Width))

#> Parameter1        |       Parameter2 |     r | t(148) |     p |        95% CI |  Method
#> ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> iris$Sepal.Length | iris$Sepal.Width | -0.12 |  -1.44 | 0.152 | [-0.27, 0.04] | Pearson

# ANOVAs
report_table(aov(Sepal.Length ~ Species, data=iris))

#> For one-way between subjects designs, partial eta squared is equvilant to eta squared.
#> Returning eta squared.
#> Parameter | Sum_Squares |  df | Mean_Square |      F |      p | Eta2 |  Eta2 90% CI
#> -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#> Species   |       63.21 |   2 |       31.61 | 119.26 | < .001 | 0.62 | [0.54, 0.68]
#> Residuals |       38.96 | 147 |        0.27 |        |        |      |             

# GLMs
report_table(lm(Sepal.Length ~ Petal.Length * Species, data = iris))

#> Warning: longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
#> Error in x$Parameter[x$Parameter == names(att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names])] <- att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names]: NAs are not allowed in subscripted assignments
report_table(glm(vs ~ disp, data = mtcars, family = "binomial"))

#> Warning: longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
#> Error in x$Parameter[x$Parameter == names(att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names])] <- att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names]: NAs are not allowed in subscripted assignments

# Mixed models
if(require("lme4")){
  model <- lme4::lmer(Sepal.Length ~ Petal.Length + (1 | Species), data = iris)
  report_table(model)
}

#> Warning: longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
#> Error in x$Parameter[x$Parameter == names(att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names])] <- att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names]: NAs are not allowed in subscripted assignments

# Bayesian models
if(require("rstanarm")){
  model <- stan_glm(Sepal.Length ~ Species, data = iris, refresh=0, iter=600)
  report_table(model, effectsize_method="basic")
}

#> Warning: longer object length is not a multiple of shorter object length
#> Error in x$Parameter[x$Parameter == names(att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names])] <- att$pretty_names[match_pretty_names]: NAs are not allowed in subscripted assignments

# Structural Equation Models (SEM)
if (require("lavaan")) {
  structure <- " ind60 =~ x1 + x2 + x3
                 dem60 =~ y1 + y2 + y3
                 dem60 ~ ind60 "
  model <- lavaan::sem(structure, data = PoliticalDemocracy)
  report_table(model)
}
